Converting value of base "tbase" into base "cbase" (in cicle) while any digit of converted value is of base "tbase" starting from "v"

Examples:

v=1000,tbase=8,cbase=10,maxdepth=100
[1][7][5][0]
[1][0][0][0]
[5][1][2]
[3][3][0]
[2][1][6]
[1][4][2]
<9><8>
Depth=5

v=2000,tbase=8,cbase=10,maxdepth=100
[3][7][2][0]
[2][0][0][0]
[1][0][2][4]
[5][3][2]
[3][4][6]
[2][3][0]
[1][5][2]
[1][0][6]
[7][0]
[5][6]
[4][6]
[3]<8>
Depth=10 (wow, 10 iterations for such small value, impressive)

v=3000,tbase=8,cbase=10,maxdepth=100
[5][6][7][0]
[3][0][0][0]
[1][5][3][6]
<8>[6][2]
Depth=2

v=4000,tbase=8,cbase=10,maxdepth=100
[7][6][4][0]
[4][0][0][0]
[2][0][4]<8>
Depth=1

v=5000,tbase=8,cbase=10,maxdepth=100
[1][1][6][0][0]
[4]<9><9>[2]
Depth=0

v=6000,tbase=8,cbase=10,maxdepth=100
[1][3][5][6][0]
[6][0][0][0]
[3][0][7][2]
[1][5]<9>[4]
Depth=2

v=7000,tbase=8,cbase=10,maxdepth=100
[1][5][5][3][0]
[7][0][0][0]
[3][5]<8>[4]
Depth=1

v=8000,tbase=8,cbase=10,maxdepth=100
[1][7][5][0][0]
<8>[0][0][0]
Depth=0

v=9000,tbase=8,cbase=10,maxdepth=100
[2][1][4][5][0]
<9>[0][0][0]
Depth=0

